<section class="section">
  <p class="small muted"><a href="/about/">← Back to About</a></p>
  <h2>TWO STRUCTURES &middot; ONE COMMUNITY</h2>
  <div class="line"></div>
  <p class="lede">The Brothers of Saint Gabriel in Thailand live and serve through two structures &mdash; one religious, one civil &mdash; carried by the same community of Brothers under one charism.</p>

  <table class="tidy" style="margin-top:24px">
    <thead>
      <tr><th></th><th>Religious Congregation</th><th>Saint Gabriel's Foundation of Thailand</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><strong>Nature</strong></td>
        <td>A pontifical-right religious institute of the Catholic Church</td>
        <td>A registered Thai foundation under civil law</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><strong>Governed by</strong></td>
        <td>Canon Law &middot; the Rule of Life &middot; the Constitutions of the Congregation &middot; Provincial Directory</td>
        <td>The Civil and Commercial Code of Thailand &middot; the Foundation's Bylaws (4th edition, 2010)</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><strong>Leader</strong></td>
        <td>Provincial Superior &middot; assisted by the Provincial Council</td>
        <td>The Provincial Superior (ex officio chair) &middot; assisted by Foundation Board members</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><strong>Members / Units</strong></td>
        <td>Approximately 72 Brothers in 19 communities</td>
        <td>15 schools in the Foundation's network &middot; six commissions</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><strong>Public face</strong></td>
        <td><strong>bsgthailand.org</strong> &middot; this site</td>
        <td><a href="https://fsgthailand.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener">fsgthailand.org</a></td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h3 style="margin-top:40px">WHY TWO STRUCTURES</h3>
  <div class="line"></div>
  <p>The Brothers' religious life — the vows, the rhythm of community, the formation of new members, the bond of spiritual brotherhood — exists under canon law of the Catholic Church. This is who we <em>are</em>.</p>
  <p>To carry the educational mission across Thailand in a manner that Thai law recognizes and that benefits Thai society, the Brothers established the <strong>Saint Gabriel's Foundation of Thailand</strong> in 1937 as a civil entity. This is how a portion of our mission <em>operates</em> in this nation.</p>

  <blockquote class="callout">
    The same community of Brothers, called by one charism, working under two legal frameworks that must remain in harmony.
  </blockquote>

  <p>Distinguishing the two structures is important for clarity &mdash; especially when corresponding with other religious congregations (a matter of canon law) or when reporting to civil authorities and educational stakeholders (a matter of civil law).</p>

  <p class="small muted" style="margin-top:24px">For the Foundation's governance, six commissions, and school network, please visit <a href="https://fsgthailand.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener">fsgthailand.org</a>.</p>
</section>

